so I asked a friend of mine

488
00:18:23,562 --> 00:18:25,562
who works in the infirmary
to check on you,

489
00:18:25,597 --> 00:18:27,542
and ten minutes ago he told me
that he's pretty damn sure

490
00:18:27,566 --> 00:18:30,333
you were gone
for at least three hours.

491
00:18:30,369 --> 00:18:31,701
<i>♪ ♪</i>

492
00:18:31,737 --> 00:18:35,505
Well, what do you have
to say about that?

493
00:18:35,541 --> 00:18:37,407
I was gone because
I was in the hospital.

494
00:18:37,442 --> 00:18:38,408
That's the first
I'm hearing about it.

495
00:18:38,443 --> 00:18:39,654
Yeah, and why
would I tell you that?

496
00:18:39,678 --> 00:18:40,644
Why wouldn't you?
Something's going on here,

497
00:18:40,679 --> 00:18:42,078
and I can tell.
All right, Kevin.

498
00:18:42,114 --> 00:18:43,725
You want to know what happened?
I went to the hospital because

499
00:18:43,749 --> 00:18:45,527
Harvey paid the doctor because
he didn't trust that I would

500
00:18:45,551 --> 00:18:47,495
make it through the night
in here, and I didn't tell you

501
00:18:47,519 --> 00:18:48,663
because I didn't want
to put you in a position

502
00:18:48,687 --> 00:18:49,864
where you'd have to lie for me.
You know what?

503
00:18:49,888 --> 00:18:51,533
That sounds like a whole lot
of bullshit to me.

504
00:18:51,557 --> 00:18:52,667
Yeah, you know what, Kevin?
I think it's pretty

505
00:18:52,691 --> 00:18:54,257
goddamn funny
that you don't trust me

506
00:18:54,293 --> 00:18:55,703
when you're the one
that won't even tell me

507
00:18:55,727 --> 00:18:56,860
what you're in here for.

508
00:18:56,895 --> 00:18:58,895
<i>♪ ♪</i>

509
00:19:02,743 --> 00:19:05,478
No. No. No.

510
00:19:05,513 --> 00:19:06,879
Shit, no.

511
00:19:06,915 --> 00:19:10,316
No. No. No.
Not now, Harvey.

512
00:19:10,351 --> 00:19:11,984
I'm in the middle
of something important.

513
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:14,554
Whatever it is,
it's not as important as this.

514
00:19:14,589 --> 00:19:16,155
What is this?

515
00:19:16,190 --> 00:19:18,369
It's notice to suspend William
Sutter's trading license.

516
00:19:18,393 --> 00:19:21,994
The question is,
what can be done about it?

517
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,440
- Nothing can be done about it.
- What do you mean,

518
00:19:23,464 --> 00:19:24,864
nothing can be done about it?

519
00:19:24,899 --> 00:19:26,243
You're supposed to be
the financial wizard.

520
00:19:26,267 --> 00:19:27,900
I am, and I'm telling you

521
00:19:27,936 --> 00:19:30,436
that this kind of thing
is at the SEC's discretion.

522
00:19:30,471 --> 00:19:31,404
They have unlimited power
to suspend

523
00:19:31,439 --> 00:19:32,905
trading licenses up to 90 days.

524
00:19:32,941 --> 00:19:34,507
- Goddamn it.
- It's only 90 days.

525
00:19:34,542 --> 00:19:36,175
90 days gets me fired.

526
00:19:36,210 --> 00:19:37,454
Well, it's gonna
be okay, Harvey.

527
00:19:37,478 --> 00:19:38,522
I mean, I know things
have been rough around here,

528
00:19:38,546 --> 00:19:39,512
but business is picking up.

529
00:19:39,547 --> 00:19:40,846
This isn't about
business, Louis.

530
00:19:40,882 --> 00:19:42,381
It's about Mike.

531
00:19:42,417 --> 00:19:44,917
<i>[tense music]</i>

532
00:19:44,953 --> 00:19:46,519
What are you not
telling me, Harvey?

533
00:19:46,554 --> 00:19:47,798
I'm not gonna tell you
the details,

534
00:19:47,822 --> 00:19:49,355
because I'm not gonna
put you at risk,

535
00:19:49,390 --> 00:19:51,524
but I have a chance
to get Mike out early,

536
00:19:51,559 --> 00:19:54,260
and if I lose this motion,
it's over.

537
00:19:54,295 --> 00:19:56,073
Well, then I'll figure out
a way to get it done.

538
00:19:56,097 --> 00:19:57,430
Thank you, Louis.

539
00:19:57,465 --> 00:20:04,136
<i>♪ ♪</i>

540
00:20:04,172 --> 00:20:06,539
[cell phone buzzing]

541
00:20:06,574 --> 00:20:08,274
This is Harvey Specter.
Harvey, it's me.

542
00:20:08,309 --> 00:20:10,876
Mike, what the hell are you
doing with a private phone?

543
00:20:10,912 --> 00:20:12,489
What the hell are you doing
representing Kevin?

544
00:20:12,513 --> 00:20:14,458
You were the one having
trouble getting him to open up.

545
00:20:14,482 --> 00:20:16,327
<i>And you thought telling him</i>
<i>not to trust anyone in here</i>

546
00:20:16,351 --> 00:20:18,484
<i>was the answer to that?</i>

547
00:20:18,519 --> 00:20:20,486
Look, I did that
to get him to trust me,

548
00:20:20,521 --> 00:20:22,888
because if he trusts me,
he trusts you.

549
00:20:22,924 --> 00:20:25,658
Yeah, well,
you didn't count on one thing.

550
00:20:25,693 --> 00:20:28,060
He knows I wasn't in
the infirmary the whole night.

551
00:20:28,096 --> 00:20:30,129
What?
How the hell does he know that?

552
00:20:30,164 --> 00:20:31,897
Some guy he knows works there.

553
00:20:31,933 --> 00:20:33,577
I told him some story about
you taking me to the hospital,

554
00:20:33,601 --> 00:20:35,301
but he's not buying it.

555
00:20:35,336 --> 00:20:37,081
Then you figure out a way
to make him buy it.

556
00:20:37,105 --> 00:20:38,337
Fine, I'll think of something,

557
00:20:38,373 --> 00:20:41,674
but that's not my only problem.

558
00:20:41,709 --> 00:20:43,109
What now?

559
00:20:43,144 --> 00:20:44,577
Gallo's filing came back.

560
00:20:44,612 --> 00:20:45,978
<i>It needs to be filed in person</i>

561
00:20:46,014 --> 00:20:48,514
and it needs to be filed
by his attorney of record.

562
00:20:48,549 --> 00:20:49,982
You got to be shitting me.

563
00:20:50,018 --> 00:20:51,951
You want me
to represent that animal?

564
00:20:51,986 --> 00:20:53,497
If you don't,
then getting Kevin to talk

565
00:20:53,521 --> 00:20:55,154
is gonna be
the least of my problems.

566
00:20:55,189 --> 00:20:57,023
[sighs]

567
00:20:57,058 --> 00:21:02,294
<i>♪ ♪</i>

568
00:21:02,330 --> 00:21:04,597
Rachel, I need your help
with something.

569
00:21:04,632 --> 00:21:06,098
What can I do?

570
00:21:06,134 --> 00:21:07,800
I need you to draft
a parole application

571
00:21:07,835 --> 00:21:08,801
for Frank Gallo.

572
00:21:08,836 --> 00:21:10,369
I thought Mike was doing that.

573
00:21:10,405 --> 00:21:12,138
There was a problem,
which is also why

574
00:21:12,173 --> 00:21:13,717
I need you to draw up
an engagement letter

575
00:21:13,741 --> 00:21:16,442
for me to be Gallo's attorney.

576
00:21:17,445 --> 00:21:18,611
Done.

577
00:21:22,417 --> 00:21:25,551
Hey, what is it?

578
00:21:25,586 --> 00:21:27,319
I heard you get upset
with Louis earlier,

579
00:21:27,355 --> 00:21:28,799
and now you're coming
to me about Gallo.

580
00:21:28,823 --> 00:21:31,791
So...I just need to know
if you think

581
00:21:31,826 --> 00:21:34,060
this whole Cahill thing's
really gonna work.

582
00:21:34,095 --> 00:21:35,061
- Rachel--
- Harvey,

583
00:21:35,096 --> 00:21:36,395
just tell me the truth.

584
00:21:36,431 --> 00:21:38,964
Look, I don't know
if it's gonna work or not,

585
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,801
but I do know
I'm not gonna stop trying.

586
00:21:41,836 --> 00:21:47,339
<i>♪ ♪</i>

587
00:21:47,375 --> 00:21:49,608
Got to say, you don't look
so bad for a guy

588
00:21:49,644 --> 00:21:51,644
who blacked out
in the yard the other day.

589
00:21:51,679 --> 00:21:53,579
Yeah, they took
good care of me.

590
00:21:53,614 --> 00:21:57,383
Well, I'm glad you're okay.
What's on your mind?

591
00:21:57,418 --> 00:21:59,385
I need you to get a message
to the warden for me.

592
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:00,786
Sure.

593
00:22:00,822 --> 00:22:02,788
I'll bring it to him
at our weekly brunch.

594
00:22:02,824 --> 00:22:04,356
What would you like
for it to say?

595
00:22:04,392 --> 00:22:05,869
- I'm serious.
- I don't care what you are.

596
00:22:05,893 --> 00:22:07,526
You want to get a message
to the warden,

597
00:22:07,562 --> 00:22:08,461
you go through
the proper channels

598
00:22:08,496 --> 00:22:09,573
and get it to him yourself.

599
00:22:09,597 --> 00:22:10,908
I can't go through
the proper channels,

600
00:22:10,932 --> 00:22:14,233
because nobody can know
about it.

601
00:22:14,268 --> 00:22:16,469
All right, Mike,
tell me what's going on.

602
00:22:19,407 --> 00:22:21,407
I made a deal
to get out of here early.

603
00:22:21,442 --> 00:22:22,708
What kind of deal?

604
00:22:22,744 --> 00:22:24,376
The kind where
I inform on someone.

605
00:22:24,412 --> 00:22:26,645
Someone?

606
00:22:26,681 --> 00:22:28,314
[sighs]
Kevin Miller.

607
00:22:28,349 --> 00:22:30,060
- Oh, Mike, come on.
- Julius, let me explain.

608
00:22:30,084 --> 00:22:31,784
I don't need you to explain.

609
00:22:31,819 --> 00:22:34,320
You are betraying your cellmate,
who you came to me to protect.

610
00:22:34,355 --> 00:22:36,489
No, what I am doing
is putting away someone

611
00:22:36,524 --> 00:22:38,402
who is out there doing
worse things than I ever did.

612
00:22:38,426 --> 00:22:40,392
So I don't need your judgment.
I need your help.

613
00:22:40,428 --> 00:22:42,895
I'm sorry, it's not my job to
help you do something like this.

614
00:22:42,930 --> 00:22:45,264
No, it's your job to help me
prepare for life after prison.

615
00:22:45,299 --> 00:22:46,844
Well, this is gonna make
life after prison

616
00:22:46,868 --> 00:22:48,567
come a hell of a lot faster.

617
00:22:48,603 --> 00:22:49,747
Well, fine,
you want to do this?

618
00:22:49,771 --> 00:22:51,682
You go ahead and do it, but
I am not gonna be complicit.

619
00:22:51,706 --> 00:22:53,506
You know what?
You talk a big goddamn game

620
00:22:53,541 --> 00:22:55,508
about trusting you,
but what does that trust mean?

621
00:22:55,543 --> 00:22:57,109
Now, I need to get
to the warden,

622
00:22:57,145 --> 00:22:59,123
and I need to do it
without the guards finding out.

623
00:22:59,147 --> 00:23:01,280
Can you help me or not?

624
00:23:01,315 --> 00:23:04,283
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

625
00:23:04,318 --> 00:23:11,323
<i>♪ ♪</i>

626
00:23:13,494 --> 00:23:15,528
Rachel, what are you
doing here so late?

627
00:23:15,563 --> 00:23:17,096
Professor,
do you have a minute?

628
00:23:17,131 --> 00:23:19,498
Of course.
Yeah, sit down.

629
00:23:25,740 --> 00:23:27,540
I went to see Leonard Bailey
this morning

630
00:23:27,575 --> 00:23:29,153
to tell him we were turning
our backs on him.

631
00:23:29,177 --> 00:23:30,876
No one's turning their back
on him, Rachel.

632
00:23:30,912 --> 00:23:32,578
There are just better cases.

633
00:23:32,613 --> 00:23:34,914
No offense,
but that's bullshit.

634
00:23:34,949 --> 00:23:37,116
- Excuse me?
- You read his file.

635
00:23:37,151 --> 00:23:39,496
There's enough evidence in there
for him to get a new trial,

636
00:23:39,520 --> 00:23:41,331
and instead we're gonna
let him rot on death row.

637
00:23:41,355 --> 00:23:42,599
Rachel, I understand
how you feel,

638
00:23:42,623 --> 00:23:44,156
but there are some things that--

639
00:23:44,192 --> 00:23:46,592
I feel like I dropped
your class to take this case.

640
00:23:46,627 --> 00:23:48,105
And I told you
I'd get you another one.

641
00:23:48,129 --> 00:23:50,596
I don't want another one.
I want this one.

642
00:23:50,631 --> 00:23:52,565
Rachel, I cannot provide you

643
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,300
with the resources
and the backing anymore.

644
00:23:54,335 --> 00:23:56,569
Okay, so what if I were able
to provide my own resources

645
00:23:56,604 --> 00:24:00,539
and--and to get the supervision
of a qualified lawyer?

646
00:24:00,575 --> 00:24:02,341
What are you talking about?

647
00:24:02,376 --> 00:24:05,010
I work at Pearson
Specter Litt, Professor.

648
00:24:05,046 --> 00:24:07,112
They've been known to take
a pro Bono case

649
00:24:07,148 --> 00:24:08,714
from time to time.

650
00:24:08,749 --> 00:24:11,350
<i>♪ ♪</i>

651
00:24:11,385 --> 00:24:12,952
Okay.

652
00:24:12,987 --> 00:24:16,255
Okay, you win, Rachel,
but this is highly irregular.

653
00:24:16,290 --> 00:24:17,923
I don't care.

654
00:24:17,959 --> 00:24:19,570
That's not a good enough reason
to turn our backs

655
00:24:19,594 --> 00:24:20,726
on Leonard Bailey.

656
00:24:20,761 --> 00:24:24,129
<i>♪ ♪</i>

657
00:24:24,165 --> 00:24:26,432
Well, don't ever question
my financial wizardry again.

658
00:24:26,467 --> 00:24:28,267
Let's have it.

659
00:24:28,302 --> 00:24:29,780
I was banging my head against
the wall, trying to figure out

660
00:24:29,804 --> 00:24:31,481
a way to stop the suspension,
but then it dawned on me.

661
00:24:31,505 --> 00:24:32,905
We don't need to stop it.

662
00:24:32,940 --> 00:24:34,551
If we can turn Sutter's firm
into the subsidiary

663
00:24:34,575 --> 00:24:36,275
of a separate holding company,

664
00:24:36,310 --> 00:24:37,955
we can find someone else
to execute the trades for him.

665
00:24:37,979 --> 00:24:39,590
- Beautiful.
- Yeah, but the only issue is,

666
00:24:39,614 --> 00:24:40,958
we need to find traders
that are willing

667
00:24:40,982 --> 00:24:41,992
to bankroll the son of a bitch,

668
00:24:42,016 --> 00:24:43,582
given his reputation.

669
00:24:43,618 --> 00:24:44,661
- Well, that's not gonna be
a problem.

670
00:24:44,685 --> 00:24:45,963
- No, Harvey,
this is not nothing.

671
00:24:45,987 --> 00:24:47,553
Nobody wants to work
with this guy.

672
00:24:47,588 --> 00:24:49,266
- You're forgetting
our new friends across the hall.

673
00:24:49,290 --> 00:24:50,656
- What?
What, are you kidding me?

674
00:24:50,691 --> 00:24:52,402
You think that asshole's
gonna say yes to me?

675
00:24:52,426 --> 00:24:55,294
- It's okay.
I know who he'll say yes to.

676
00:24:55,329 --> 00:24:57,196
<i>♪ ♪</i>

677
00:24:57,231 --> 00:24:58,831
- Hey, Harvey,

678
00:24:58,866 --> 00:25:00,711
I know how tough it's been
not having Mike here,

679
00:25:00,735 --> 00:25:03,936
and I just want to let you know
that I miss him too.

680
00:25:03,971 --> 00:25:05,782
- I appreciate that, Louis,
but you didn't have to say it,

681
00:25:05,806 --> 00:25:07,373
because actions speak louder
than words,

682
00:25:07,408 --> 00:25:09,909
and you doing this says it all.

683
00:25:09,944 --> 00:25:11,944
<i>♪ ♪</i>

684
00:25:17,813 --> 00:25:19,814
Harvey, I've been looking
for you all day.

685
00:25:19,849 --> 00:25:21,315
Well, here I am.

686
00:25:21,351 --> 00:25:23,251
Then maybe you can tell me
why all of a sudden

687
00:25:23,286 --> 00:25:24,752
we're representing
William Sutter.

688
00:25:24,788 --> 00:25:26,954
- I changed my mind.
- You changed your mind?

689
00:25:26,990 --> 00:25:30,992
You told me taking Sutter on
would be like selling your soul,

690
00:25:31,027 --> 00:25:32,338
and now you're doing
a complete 180.

691
00:25:32,362 --> 00:25:33,327
Jessica, I--

692
00:25:33,363 --> 00:25:35,163
No, Harvey,

693
00:25:35,198 --> 00:25:36,631
I'm not saying I don't like it.

694
00:25:36,666 --> 00:25:38,132
I just want to know
what's going on.

695
00:25:38,168 --> 00:25:40,868
Sutter's the one
Cahill's after.

696
00:25:40,904 --> 00:25:42,170
Oh, you've got
to be kidding me.

697
00:25:42,205 --> 00:25:43,871
I shit you not.

698
00:25:43,907 --> 00:25:47,008
Oh, well, I get it.

699
00:25:47,043 --> 00:25:49,010
You give him
a full-throttle defense,

700
00:25:49,045 --> 00:25:50,278
gain his trust,

701
00:25:50,313 --> 00:25:52,346
and hope to God Mike
cuts his legs out.

702
00:25:52,382 --> 00:25:54,816
Exactly.

703
00:25:54,851 --> 00:25:56,150
What?

704
00:25:56,186 --> 00:25:58,086
Is he gonna give us
his investment business?

705
00:25:58,121 --> 00:25:59,754
Not until after we win.

706
00:25:59,789 --> 00:26:01,255
Which we're hoping we don't.

707
00:26:01,291 --> 00:26:03,791
- Jessica, I have to do this.
- Harvey, relax.

708
00:26:03,827 --> 00:26:05,727
I'm on board.
It pays the bills,

709
00:26:05,762 --> 00:26:07,673
and we can leverage it
into more business anyway,

710
00:26:07,697 --> 00:26:09,997
but we'd better
leverage it fast,

711
00:26:10,033 --> 00:26:11,844
because losing this case
might be good for Mike,

712
00:26:11,868 --> 00:26:14,068
but it's not gonna
be good for us,

713
00:26:14,104 --> 00:26:15,269
and I don't know about you,

714
00:26:15,305 --> 00:26:17,105
but I'd like to get back on top.

715
00:26:17,140 --> 00:26:20,174
There's nothing I'd like more,
which is why I came in here.

716
00:26:20,210 --> 00:26:21,743
What do you need?

717
00:26:21,778 --> 00:26:24,112
I need you to get something
from those traders.

718
00:26:24,147 --> 00:26:27,415
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

719
00:26:27,450 --> 00:26:29,417
[door buzzes]

720
00:26:29,452 --> 00:26:31,652
On your feet, Ross.
You're going to solitary.

721
00:26:31,688 --> 00:26:33,199
What? Wait,
what are you talking about?

722
00:26:33,223 --> 00:26:35,156
You heard me.
24 hours, let's go.

723
00:26:35,191 --> 00:26:36,702
No, I'm not going anywhere
with you until you tell me

724
00:26:36,726 --> 00:26:38,504
what's going on.
You'll go where I tell you to,

725
00:26:38,528 --> 00:26:40,128
or you'll get acquainted
with this.

726
00:26:40,163 --> 00:26:41,829
Listen to me.
I just want to know why--

727
00:26:41,865 --> 00:26:45,533
Next question
makes it 48 hours.

728
00:26:45,568 --> 00:26:47,135
You coming or not?

729
00:26:47,170 --> 00:26:49,137
<i>♪ ♪</i>

730
00:26:49,172 --> 00:26:50,638
What did you do?

731
00:26:50,673 --> 00:26:58,379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

732
00:26:58,414 --> 00:26:59,781
Jessica--good, I caught you.

733
00:26:59,816 --> 00:27:01,449
Rachel, what is it?

734
00:27:01,484 --> 00:27:03,124
Do you remember
my Innocence Project case?

735
00:27:03,153 --> 00:27:05,253
How could I not?
Badass Rachel.

736
00:27:05,288 --> 00:27:07,288
Well, thank you.

737
00:27:07,323 --> 00:27:09,135
So I took it, but now they're
saying that it doesn't qualify.

738
00:27:09,159 --> 00:27:10,458
Let me guess.

739
00:27:10,493 --> 00:27:12,226
You want us to take it on
as a pro Bono.

740
00:27:12,262 --> 00:27:14,295
All I need is one hour
a week of supervision,

741
00:27:14,330 --> 00:27:16,931
and if I need to appear
in court, you come with me.

742
00:27:16,966 --> 00:27:18,900
I know that that's a lot
to ask, but--

743
00:27:18,935 --> 00:27:21,769
Rachel, I wish I could tell
you I had an extra hour to give,

744
00:27:21,805 --> 00:27:23,604
but I don't.
Jessica, please.

745
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:25,173
If you would
just come with me

746
00:27:25,208 --> 00:27:27,675
and meet this man--
No, this is my point.

747
00:27:27,710 --> 00:27:29,944
I just found out we have
less time than I thought we did

748
00:27:29,979 --> 00:27:31,512
to get this firm
back on its feet,

749
00:27:31,548 --> 00:27:34,482
and I can't afford to spend
one minute on anything else.

750
00:27:34,517 --> 00:27:35,616
But, I mean, really--

751
00:27:35,652 --> 00:27:40,121
Rachel, I'm sorry.

752
00:27:40,156 --> 00:27:41,956
Now if you'll excuse me.

753
00:27:41,991 --> 00:27:49,997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

754
00:27:56,639 --> 00:27:57,972
Thank you.

755
00:27:58,007 --> 00:27:59,941
Thank your counselor,
Mr. Rowe.

756
00:27:59,976 --> 00:28:01,376
- I will.
- You must trust him a lot

757
00:28:01,411 --> 00:28:04,078
to let him in on
your little arrangement.

758
00:28:04,113 --> 00:28:05,813
I do.

759
00:28:05,849 --> 00:28:09,383
He helped me, even though
he doesn't approve of this.

760
00:28:09,419 --> 00:28:10,952
Sounds like you don't either.

761
00:28:10,987 --> 00:28:12,231
- It's not up to me
to approve or not.

762
00:28:12,255 --> 00:28:14,088
Is that what you
came down here to tell me?

763
00:28:14,123 --> 00:28:15,467
No, I came down here
to tell you I've been doing this

764
00:28:15,491 --> 00:28:17,225
a long time,

765
00:28:17,260 --> 00:28:20,394
and I've seen a lot
of inmates come and go.

766
00:28:20,430 --> 00:28:23,397
These kind of deals, they don't
always work out so well.

767
00:28:23,433 --> 00:28:25,678
You saying you think I'll be
here for the whole two years?

768
00:28:25,702 --> 00:28:29,170
I'm saying I hope it doesn't
turn out even worse than that.

769
00:28:29,205 --> 00:28:37,211
<i>♪ ♪</i>

770
00:28:49,058 --> 00:28:51,292
I thought the markets
were closed.

771
00:28:51,327 --> 00:28:52,471
Did you ever see
"Wall Street"?

772
00:28:52,495 --> 00:28:54,428
Money never sleeps.

773
00:28:56,666 --> 00:29:00,234
What's this?
Have a look.

774
00:29:00,270 --> 00:29:01,614
Let me get this straight.
I hire you,

775
00:29:01,638 --> 00:29:03,549
and the first thing you do
is come to me for a favor?

776
00:29:03,573 --> 00:29:06,207
I came to you for a favor
when you were my tenant.

777
00:29:06,242 --> 00:29:09,210
Now, as your lawyer, I am coming
to you with an opportunity.

778
00:29:09,245 --> 00:29:10,044
What are you talking about?

779
00:29:10,079 --> 00:29:12,046
That's not
a charitable donation.

780
00:29:12,081 --> 00:29:14,048
You do this,
you'll get paid for it.

781
00:29:14,083 --> 00:29:15,616
- How much?
- Enough.

782
00:29:15,652 --> 00:29:17,329
How do I know I'm not
leaving something on the table?

783
00:29:17,353 --> 00:29:19,987
Because I never leave
anything on the table.

784
00:29:21,491 --> 00:29:22,990
All right.

785
00:29:26,129 --> 00:29:28,663
You know, I don't get it.

786
00:29:28,698 --> 00:29:30,431
You're obviously
a big-time attorney,

787
00:29:30,466 --> 00:29:33,167
and now you're subletting to me.

788
00:29:33,202 --> 00:29:35,303
What the hell happened here?

789
00:29:35,338 --> 00:29:37,738
- You don't know?
- Why would I?

790
00:29:37,774 --> 00:29:40,274
- Google it.
- That bad?

791
00:29:40,310 --> 00:29:42,109
We hired a lawyer.

792
00:29:42,145 --> 00:29:44,845
Turns out he was a fraud.
It ruined our reputation.

793
00:29:44,881 --> 00:29:48,249
Turned out to be a fraud,
or you knew he was a fraud?

794
00:29:48,284 --> 00:29:51,285
Good night, Stu.
See you in the morning.

795
00:29:51,321 --> 00:29:59,327
<i>♪ ♪</i>

796
00:30:00,563 --> 00:30:03,297
[door buzzes, opens]

797
00:30:03,333 --> 00:30:04,944
Warden, what are you--
what are you doing?

798
00:30:04,968 --> 00:30:06,100
Did you know Mike Ross

799
00:30:06,135 --> 00:30:07,479
left the prison grounds
the other night?

800
00:30:07,503 --> 00:30:08,769
- What?
- Don't bullshit me.

801
00:30:08,805 --> 00:30:10,316
Did you know his lawyer,
who I understand

802
00:30:10,340 --> 00:30:11,706
is now also your lawyer,

803
00:30:11,741 --> 00:30:13,207
paid someone to get him
out of here?

804
00:30:13,242 --> 00:30:14,208
I don't know
anything about it.

805
00:30:14,243 --> 00:30:15,609
I suppose if I asked you

806
00:30:15,645 --> 00:30:18,479
who he paid,
you'd have the same answer.

807
00:30:18,514 --> 00:30:20,948
I find out you're lying,
next time,

808
00:30:20,984 --> 00:30:23,017
you are gonna be
the one in solitary,

809
00:30:23,052 --> 00:30:24,952
and it won't be just one night.

810
00:30:24,988 --> 00:30:31,525
<i>♪ ♪</i>

811
00:30:31,561 --> 00:30:32,526
[door slams shut]

812
00:30:32,562 --> 00:30:33,761
<i>♪ ♪</i>

813
00:30:38,803 --> 00:30:41,504
<i>[mellow music]</i>

814
00:30:41,540 --> 00:30:48,845
<i>♪ ♪</i>

815
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:50,180
- What?
- I'm just thinking about

816
00:30:50,215 --> 00:30:51,781
when this asshole finds out

817
00:30:51,817 --> 00:30:54,250
you're gonna blow his bullshit
suspension out of the water.

818
00:30:54,286 --> 00:30:57,087
William, I am gonna
blow it out of the water,

819
00:30:57,122 --> 00:31:00,490
but I'm gonna need you
to sign this first.

820
00:31:02,361 --> 00:31:04,160
What the hell is
Stevens Investment Group?

821
00:31:04,196 --> 00:31:06,296
It's the company you're
trading through from now on.

822
00:31:06,331 --> 00:31:08,331
Bullshit.
They own me?

823
00:31:08,367 --> 00:31:09,766
They don't own anything.

824
00:31:09,801 --> 00:31:11,301
They control you on paper,

825
00:31:11,336 --> 00:31:14,003
and unless you want to shut down
for the next 90 days,

826
00:31:14,039 --> 00:31:15,004
this is what you have to do.

827
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:16,306
Well, bullshit.

828
00:31:16,341 --> 00:31:18,341
What are you gonna do
if that guy indicts me,

829
00:31:18,377 --> 00:31:20,477
cut a deal where I plead guilty,
and I get probation?

830
00:31:20,512 --> 00:31:22,412
'Cause if this is
what you consider winning,

831
00:31:22,447 --> 00:31:24,025
I might as well
find myself another lawyer.

832
00:31:24,049 --> 00:31:27,283
Okay, gentlemen,
I'm ready to hear arguments,

833
00:31:27,319 --> 00:31:28,918
but I have to tell you,

834
00:31:28,954 --> 00:31:31,187
unless Congress passed
a new law last night,

835
00:31:31,223 --> 00:31:32,789
this suspension stands.

836
00:31:37,028 --> 00:31:38,161
That's okay, Your Honor.

837
00:31:38,196 --> 00:31:40,130
My client's firm is now

838
00:31:40,165 --> 00:31:41,765
the subsidiary
of a holding company

839
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:43,366
with a different
trading license.

840
00:31:43,402 --> 00:31:45,435
- What?
- It's all right here.

841
00:31:45,470 --> 00:31:46,803
In that case, I move

842
00:31:46,838 --> 00:31:48,438
to have that
company's license suspended.

843
00:31:48,473 --> 00:31:50,774
And that, right there,
is why I'd like to ask the court

844
00:31:50,809 --> 00:31:52,208
to have Mr. Cahill removed

845
00:31:52,244 --> 00:31:53,376
from any investigation

846
00:31:53,412 --> 00:31:54,944
regarding my client
in the future.

847
00:31:54,980 --> 00:31:56,780
Are you out of your mind?

848
00:31:56,815 --> 00:31:59,582
We have an antagonistic
history, Your Honor.

849
00:31:59,618 --> 00:32:01,785
Everyone knows it,
and this action

850
00:32:01,820 --> 00:32:03,286
is nothing more than a stunt

851
00:32:03,321 --> 00:32:05,288
designed to punish me
through my client.

852
00:32:05,323 --> 00:32:06,589
This is ridiculous.

853
00:32:06,625 --> 00:32:08,436
I've been investigating
William Sutter for 18 months.

854
00:32:08,460 --> 00:32:09,959
And in the last 18 months,

855
00:32:09,995 --> 00:32:11,227
he took no action,

856
00:32:11,263 --> 00:32:13,396
and then yesterday,
when I informed him

857
00:32:13,432 --> 00:32:14,898
I am Mr. Sutter's attorney,

858
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:17,467
within five hours
he suspends his license,

859
00:32:17,502 --> 00:32:20,470
and now he's trying
to do it again.

860
00:32:20,505 --> 00:32:22,405
That's what I call a win.

861
00:32:22,441 --> 00:32:24,407
Mr. Cahill,
this doesn't look good.

862
00:32:24,443 --> 00:32:26,176
I'm inclined
to take you off this case.

863
00:32:26,211 --> 00:32:28,411
Your Honor,
Mr. Specter is right.

864
00:32:28,447 --> 00:32:30,413
We have history,
but I've been involved

865
00:32:30,449 --> 00:32:31,926
in this case
a lot longer than he has.

866
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:33,917
So if anyone has to be
thrown out for a conflict,

867
00:32:33,952 --> 00:32:35,285
it is him, not me.

868
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:36,853
I'm not going anywhere,
Your Honor.

869
00:32:36,888 --> 00:32:38,121
Then let Mr. Sutter waive

870
00:32:38,156 --> 00:32:39,589
any claims
to conflict altogether,

871
00:32:39,624 --> 00:32:41,302
unless, of course,
you want to set a precedent

872
00:32:41,326 --> 00:32:43,493
that any time a defendant
doesn't like his prosecutor,

873
00:32:43,528 --> 00:32:44,928
all he has to do
is hire a lawyer

874
00:32:44,963 --> 00:32:47,430
he's gone up against before.

875
00:32:47,466 --> 00:32:50,200
Mr. Sutter, would you like
to keep your attorney

876
00:32:50,235 --> 00:32:51,646
or hire another one,
because I am not

877
00:32:51,670 --> 00:32:54,237
taking Mr. Cahill off this case.

878
00:32:54,272 --> 00:32:57,240
<i>[tense music]</i>

879
00:32:57,275 --> 00:32:59,075
<i>♪ ♪</i>

880
00:32:59,110 --> 00:33:02,245
Harvey's my guy, Your Honor.

881
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:03,720
Then unless there's
some other issue,

882
00:33:03,748 --> 00:33:05,648
the court has a full docket.

883
00:33:05,684 --> 00:33:07,283
[gavel bangs]

884
00:33:07,319 --> 00:33:15,325
<i>♪ ♪</i>

885
00:33:21,333 --> 00:33:22,677
Guard tells you
you have a visitor,

886
00:33:22,701 --> 00:33:24,278
doesn't say who it is,
you start thinking

887
00:33:24,302 --> 00:33:26,903
maybe Angelina Jolie
opened your letters after all.

888
00:33:26,938 --> 00:33:28,271
Sit down, Gallo.

889
00:33:28,306 --> 00:33:30,473
You here to make
more false accusations?

890
00:33:30,509 --> 00:33:32,475
I'm here to tell you that,
as of this minute,

891
00:33:32,511 --> 00:33:34,344
I'm your new attorney.

892
00:33:34,379 --> 00:33:35,411
Come again?

893
00:33:35,447 --> 00:33:37,480
You need someone
to file that motion.

894
00:33:37,516 --> 00:33:39,349
I'm that someone.

895
00:33:39,384 --> 00:33:40,650
What if I don't want
your help?

896
00:33:40,685 --> 00:33:43,453
Well, then you can rot in here
for the rest of your sentence.

897
00:33:46,324 --> 00:33:48,491
It's actually
kind of funny, isn't it,

898
00:33:48,527 --> 00:33:50,260
you fighting to get me out

899
00:33:50,295 --> 00:33:53,229
when you fought so hard
to put me away.

900
00:33:53,265 --> 00:33:54,564
Must kill you.

901
00:33:54,599 --> 00:33:57,133
Makes me sick to my stomach,

902
00:33:57,168 --> 00:33:59,369
but I'm gonna live with it,

903
00:33:59,404 --> 00:34:01,404
because you're gonna give me
something in return.

904
00:34:01,439 --> 00:34:03,373
Oh, yeah?
What's that?

905
00:34:03,408 --> 00:34:04,807
Until this thing goes through,

906
00:34:04,843 --> 00:34:07,410
not only are you gonna
keep your hands off Mike,

907
00:34:07,445 --> 00:34:09,379
you're gonna be his personal
protector in here.

908
00:34:09,414 --> 00:34:10,613
- Bullshit.
- Not bullshit.

909
00:34:10,649 --> 00:34:13,216
He so much as twists
an ankle in the yard,

910
00:34:13,251 --> 00:34:14,951
I'll withdraw that motion.

911
00:34:14,986 --> 00:34:17,220
Now, aren't you forgetting
a little something, champ?

912
00:34:17,255 --> 00:34:19,389
I don't need you
to handle this thing for me.

913
00:34:19,424 --> 00:34:21,558
Now that I know what's what,
I'll get my own attorney.

914
00:34:21,593 --> 00:34:23,760
Yeah, you do that,
and I'll tell the courts

915
00:34:23,795 --> 00:34:27,230
that you just admitted to me
that you tried to poison Mike.

916
00:34:27,265 --> 00:34:28,776
You know how much time that's
gonna add to your sentence?

917
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:30,440
- I didn't do shit to him!
- Good for you.

918
00:34:30,468 --> 00:34:32,168
Who do you think
they're gonna believe,

919
00:34:32,203 --> 00:34:33,770
a former prosecutor like me

920
00:34:33,805 --> 00:34:37,407
or an informant convict
like you?

921
00:34:37,442 --> 00:34:40,310
Of course, if I'm your attorney,

922
00:34:40,345 --> 00:34:42,245
I can't tell them any of that.

923
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:44,280
[chuckles]

924
00:34:44,316 --> 00:34:46,349
You son of a bitch.

925
00:34:46,384 --> 00:34:47,350
You set me up.

926
00:34:47,385 --> 00:34:49,652
I sure as hell did.

927
00:34:49,688 --> 00:34:52,589
So it's up to you.

928
00:34:52,624 --> 00:34:55,191
You in or you out?

929
00:34:55,226 --> 00:34:58,227
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

930
00:35:02,801 --> 00:35:04,233
Can I talk to you a second?

931
00:35:04,269 --> 00:35:06,402
What is it, Louis?

932
00:35:06,438 --> 00:35:07,604
I can't find a house.

933
00:35:07,639 --> 00:35:09,973
A house?
What house?

934
00:35:10,008 --> 00:35:11,252
I don't know anything
about a house,

935
00:35:11,276 --> 00:35:12,775
certainly not for a person

936
00:35:12,811 --> 00:35:14,488
who doesn't have
any confidence in my ability

937
00:35:14,512 --> 00:35:16,257
to know what he's looking for
in a given situation.

938
00:35:16,281 --> 00:35:18,092
Donna, please, can't we just
pretend that I didn't say

939
00:35:18,116 --> 00:35:19,582
what I said, like we usually do?

940
00:35:19,618 --> 00:35:21,228
No, Louis, we can't,
because I need to know

941
00:35:21,252 --> 00:35:23,331
that you have spent at least
one second contemplating

942
00:35:23,355 --> 00:35:25,288
what your little
outburst was about.

943
00:35:31,463 --> 00:35:33,596
I know what it was about.

944
00:35:33,632 --> 00:35:35,064
Really?
What is that?

945
00:35:35,100 --> 00:35:37,300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

946
00:35:37,335 --> 00:35:40,269
I miss you, Donna.

947
00:35:40,305 --> 00:35:43,940
I miss having you
as my secretary.

948
00:35:43,975 --> 00:35:47,443
<i>♪ ♪</i>

949
00:35:47,479 --> 00:35:49,178
I miss you too, Louis.

950
00:35:49,214 --> 00:35:50,279
And don't get me wrong.

951
00:35:50,315 --> 00:35:51,325
I'm not saying
Gretchen's not great.

952
00:35:51,349 --> 00:35:52,949
Who would?

953
00:35:52,984 --> 00:35:57,120
It's just--I'm just saying
she's not you.

954
00:35:57,155 --> 00:35:58,888
- Who is?
- Nobody.

955
00:35:58,923 --> 00:36:05,128
<i>♪ ♪</i>

956
00:36:05,163 --> 00:36:06,941
Was this the kind of thing
you're looking for?

957
00:36:06,965 --> 00:36:09,265
Oh, my God, it's perfect.
Is it still available?

958
00:36:09,300 --> 00:36:11,312
- An offer went in this morning.
- We have to beat it.

959
00:36:11,336 --> 00:36:13,569
No, Louis, we don't.

960
00:36:13,605 --> 00:36:15,071
That offer was yours.

961
00:36:15,106 --> 00:36:18,875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

962
00:36:18,910 --> 00:36:20,309
Did they take it?

963
00:36:20,345 --> 00:36:21,444
We find out tomorrow.

964
00:36:21,479 --> 00:36:23,880
[laughs]

965
00:36:23,915 --> 00:36:26,315
Donna--
No.

966
00:36:26,351 --> 00:36:29,585
<i>♪ ♪</i>

967
00:36:29,621 --> 00:36:31,421
[door buzzes]

968
00:36:36,361 --> 00:36:38,361
[sighs]

969
00:36:41,433 --> 00:36:43,233
I'm sorry about what happened
with the warden.

970
00:36:43,268 --> 00:36:44,467
Yeah.

971
00:36:46,771 --> 00:36:48,337
If you need anything--

972
00:36:48,373 --> 00:36:49,373
I'll let you know.

973
00:36:57,749 --> 00:36:59,248
Look, I didn't--
I didn't tell them

974
00:36:59,284 --> 00:37:02,118
what you told me
about Harvey getting you out.

975
00:37:02,153 --> 00:37:04,420
I need you to know that.
It's important to me.

976
00:37:04,456 --> 00:37:06,889
Yeah, whatever you say, Kevin.

977
00:37:09,561 --> 00:37:12,228
I know I haven't told you
why I'm in here, Mike...

978
00:37:15,433 --> 00:37:17,200
But you don't understand.

979
00:37:17,235 --> 00:37:19,402
From the second I got here,
I've had to watch

980
00:37:19,437 --> 00:37:22,605
what I say, every single word,

981
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:23,806
and every morning I get up,

982
00:37:23,842 --> 00:37:25,374
and I remind myself

983
00:37:25,410 --> 00:37:27,744
not to say the wrong thing
to the wrong person,

984
00:37:27,779 --> 00:37:31,314
and every night
I go to bed and think,

985
00:37:31,349 --> 00:37:33,149
"Another day down
where I didn't."

986
00:37:33,184 --> 00:37:36,753
Yeah, you think I don't know
what that's like?

987
00:37:36,788 --> 00:37:38,888
I've been living a lie
every day for years.

988
00:37:38,923 --> 00:37:42,825
Yeah, but you were
just protecting yourself.

989
00:37:42,861 --> 00:37:45,361
You don't have a family.

990
00:37:49,300 --> 00:37:52,902
Kevin, what did you do?

991
00:37:58,443 --> 00:38:00,610
I got in a fight with my wife.

992
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:04,614
It was...

993
00:38:04,649 --> 00:38:07,183
it was bad.

994
00:38:07,218 --> 00:38:09,185
We said things to each other
we never said before.

995
00:38:09,220 --> 00:38:13,289
I went out.

996
00:38:13,324 --> 00:38:15,591
I got drunk.

997
00:38:15,627 --> 00:38:17,026
I got into my car,

998
00:38:17,061 --> 00:38:21,731
and I almost killed someone.

999
00:38:21,766 --> 00:38:23,410
Next thing I knew,
I woke up in an ambulance,

1000
00:38:23,434 --> 00:38:25,134
looking up at a police officer.

1001
00:38:25,170 --> 00:38:28,104
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1002
00:38:28,139 --> 00:38:29,438
What?

1003
00:38:29,474 --> 00:38:32,642
I made one stupid,

1004
00:38:32,677 --> 00:38:34,477
stupid mistake.

1005
00:38:34,512 --> 00:38:37,313
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1006
00:38:37,348 --> 00:38:41,317
And it's gonna cost me
three years with my family,

1007
00:38:41,352 --> 00:38:44,253
and it's not just
the special things, man.

1008
00:38:44,289 --> 00:38:46,122
I'm missing a thousand chances

1009
00:38:46,157 --> 00:38:49,292
to hug my kids in the morning...

1010
00:38:49,327 --> 00:38:52,428
[choking up]
And kiss my wife good night,

1011
00:38:52,463 --> 00:38:55,531
all because I couldn't
control myself.

1012
00:38:55,567 --> 00:38:57,667
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1013
00:38:57,702 --> 00:39:00,670
What were you fighting
with your wife about?

1014
00:39:00,705 --> 00:39:03,873
What do you mean, you were
trying to protect your family?

1015
00:39:03,908 --> 00:39:05,174
Kevin.

1016
00:39:05,210 --> 00:39:09,345
[crying]
I--yeah, I can't.

1017
00:39:09,380 --> 00:39:10,746
I just can't.

1018
00:39:10,782 --> 00:39:18,788
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1019
00:39:23,928 --> 00:39:31,267
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1020
00:39:31,302 --> 00:39:34,203
Okay.

1021
00:39:34,239 --> 00:39:36,272
I'll do it.

1022
00:39:36,307 --> 00:39:38,474
- Excuse me?
- Your pro Bono.

1023
00:39:38,509 --> 00:39:40,243
Bring me the file
tomorrow morning.

1024
00:39:41,646 --> 00:39:45,047
Jessica, I'm sorry.
Can I just ask why?

1025
00:39:45,083 --> 00:39:47,149
What does it matter?

1026
00:39:47,185 --> 00:39:48,985
It matters to me.

1027
00:39:49,020 --> 00:39:50,286
I've been out all day,

1028
00:39:50,321 --> 00:39:54,223
trying to drum up business,
and it hasn't been easy.

1029
00:39:54,259 --> 00:39:56,425
So from now on,
when people Google our name,

1030
00:39:56,461 --> 00:39:59,061
I'd rather they see,

1031
00:39:59,097 --> 00:40:03,266
"innocent man freed
by Pearson Specter"

1032
00:40:03,301 --> 00:40:05,902
than "Manhattan law firm
hires a fraud."

1033
00:40:05,937 --> 00:40:07,403
<i>[stirring music]</i>

1034
00:40:07,438 --> 00:40:09,672
Thank you.

1035
00:40:09,707 --> 00:40:11,340
Good night, Rachel.

1036
00:40:11,376 --> 00:40:18,814
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1037
00:40:18,850 --> 00:40:20,349
What are you doing here, Sean?

1038
00:40:20,385 --> 00:40:22,418
Oh, you know
what I'm doing here.

1039
00:40:22,453 --> 00:40:23,453
What were you thinking,

1040
00:40:23,488 --> 00:40:24,632
trying to get me
thrown off my own case?

1041
00:40:24,656 --> 00:40:26,155
He was coming at me.

1042
00:40:26,190 --> 00:40:27,957
I had to do something
to keep his trust.

1043
00:40:27,992 --> 00:40:30,293
Well, for your information,
if I get thrown off this case,

1044
00:40:30,328 --> 00:40:32,339
that deal that you don't know
about getting that certain

1045
00:40:32,363 --> 00:40:34,430
someone out early
doesn't exist anymore.

1046
00:40:34,465 --> 00:40:36,966
- You think I don't know that?
- No, I don't think you do,

1047
00:40:37,001 --> 00:40:38,879
because if I hadn't pulled
that shit out of my ass,

1048
00:40:38,903 --> 00:40:41,537
this whole thing
would've been for nothing.

1049
00:40:41,572 --> 00:40:43,773
What are you so pleased
with yourself about?

1050
00:40:43,808 --> 00:40:45,341
Nothing.
It's just...

1051
00:40:45,376 --> 00:40:47,476
you didn't want me
to take this case,

1052
00:40:47,512 --> 00:40:48,856
and now you're getting
pissed at me

1053
00:40:48,880 --> 00:40:52,648
because I'm too good a job
defending my client.

1054
00:40:52,684 --> 00:40:55,318
Now that you put it
that way...

1055
00:40:55,353 --> 00:40:57,086
It was a good fix, Sean.

1056
00:40:57,121 --> 00:40:58,888
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1057
00:40:59,423 --> 00:41:01,757
- It was a good move, Harvey.
- Want to get a drink?

1058
00:41:01,792 --> 00:41:02,758
Why don't we
just have one here?

1059
00:41:02,793 --> 00:41:05,354
This might be the last one that
we have together for a long time.

1060
00:41:06,185 --> 00:41:06,817
Why?

1061
00:41:06,841 --> 00:41:07,520
As of right now,

1062
00:41:07,544 --> 00:41:09,682
you have no action
pending against my client.

1063
00:41:09,965 --> 00:41:12,324
But as of tomorrow, I do,

1064
00:41:12,348 --> 00:41:14,998
'cause those indictments
are coming down in the morning.

1065
00:41:15,339 --> 00:41:16,739
[glasses clink]

